<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.24" />

<fw type="curatorial">24</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
May 8, 1973
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. and Mrs. George Schottenhamel</addrLine>
<addrLine>Peru State College</addrLine>
<addrLine>Peru, Nebraska 68421</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Mr. and Mrs. Schottenhamel:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Replying to your letter of May 4, 1973, we here would be delighted to have you and your touring students stop for a visit on the afternoon of May 22.</p>

<p>The "soft spot in my heart" for Peru students is still there, and it would be a special pleasure for me to welcome them here. Mrs. Young is writing a note to you.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With all kind thoughts, your friend,</salute>


<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>

<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

